lzh_formatted:
  title: 題梁州客舍壁
  author: 鄭誧
  language: lzh
  text: 五更燈影照殘粧。欲話別離先斷膓。落月半庭推戶出。杏花踈影滿衣裳。
korean:
  title: 제양주객사벽
  author: 정포
  language: kor
  text: |-
    오경의 등불 그림자 일그러진 단장을 비출 때
    이별을 이야기하려니 먼저 창자가 끊어지네
    반 뜰의 지는 달빛에 문을 밀고 나가 보니
    살구꽃 성긴 그림자 가득히 옷에 차네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0800&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Written on the Wall of a Traveler's Lodge in Liangzhou
  author: Jung Po
  language: eng
  text: |-
    At the fifth watch, lamplight casts shadows on a beauty's disheveled face.
    Wishing to speak of parting, my heart breaks before words can form.
    Through the half-lit courtyard, I push open the door and step out—
    Sparse apricot blossoms' shadows scatter across my robe.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'fifth watch' refers to the period just before dawn, evoking the melancholy of an imminent departure.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem plays on the tension between the desire to speak and the overwhelming emotion that prevents it—a common motif in classical poetry about separation and longing.
